# Docker (Orbit Wars eval / Kaggle)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `tools/docker.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/tools/docker.mdc).

## Submit-valid order

- Packaging/Docker validate **before** tournament ladder: `ow eval package --checkpoint ... --validate-docker` (JSON `"ok": true`).
- Hybrid promotion: `artifacts=hybrid_promotion` → async `checkpoint_eval` (Docker → tournament → promote).

## Dockerfile habits

- Pin base image tags (no `:latest`).
- Multi-stage builds: builder with dev deps, runtime with only agent artifacts.
- `.dockerignore`: exclude `.git`, `outputs/`, tests, large checkpoints not needed in the image.
- Non-root `USER` in runtime stage when compatible with Kaggle agent layout.

## Security

- No secrets in image layers; use runtime env / mounted secrets.
- Never commit `.env` with credentials.

## Debugging

- Poll `ow eval status --run <path> --watch`; inspect `evaluations/checkpoint_eval_*/docker_validation/`.
- Local replay HTML alone is not submit-valid proof.
